defaultMonitoring performance and ensuring efficiency gainsdefault - 
defaultbenchmarking data shows that by bringing the bottom 25% of farms in the UK up to the technical efficiency performance of the average, dairy output would increase by 9%,. Similarly, increasing the average to the top 25% would mean an extra 34% output.
defaultb)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultConfidencedefault - 
defaultthe NFU believes that if dairy farmers had the confidence to invest (we suggest that on average farmers should be investing 3.5ppl per year in infrastructure) then improvements to efficiency and increasing output can be achieved.
